00:00:51.860 --> 00:00:56.960
So in less than 200 years Islam went from
not existing to being the religious and political

00:00:56.960 --> 00:01:00.639
organizing principal of one of the largest
empires in the world.

00:01:00.639 --> 00:01:05.100
And that story begins in the 7th century CE
when the angel Gabriel appeared to Muhammad,

00:01:05.100 --> 00:01:10.840
a 40-ish guy who made his living as a caravan
trader and told him to begin reciting the word of God.

00:01:10.840 --> 00:01:14.540
Initially, this freaked Muhammad out, as,
you know, it would—but then his wife and

00:01:14.540 --> 00:01:18.800
a couple of other people encouraged him and
slowly he came to accept the mantle as prophet.

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:23.290
A few things to know about the world Islam
entered: First, Muhammad’s society was intensely

00:01:23.290 --> 00:01:28.820
tribal. He was a member of the Quraysh tribe,
living in Mecca and tribal ties were extremely important.

00:01:28.820 --> 00:01:33.090
Also, at the time, the Arabian peninsula was
like this crazy religious melting pot. Like

00:01:33.090 --> 00:01:39.370
most tribal Arabs worshipped gods very similar to the
Mesopotamian gods you’ll remember from episode 3.

00:01:39.370 --> 00:01:43.000
And by the time of Muhammad, cult statutes
of many of those gods had been collected in

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:47.040
his hometown of Mecca in this temple-like
structure called the Kaaba.

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:50.690
But Arabia was also a home for monotheisms
like Christianity and Judaism, even a bit

00:01:50.690 --> 00:01:55.840
of Zoroastrianism. So the message that there
was only god wouldn’t have been like as

00:01:55.840 --> 00:01:59.000
surprising to Muhammad as it was, for instance,
to Abraham.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:02.530
Also, and this will become very important,
the northern part of Arabia was sandwiched

00:02:02.530 --> 00:02:07.030
between the Byzantine Empire and the Persian
Sassanian Empire—and you’ll remember,

00:02:07.030 --> 00:02:12.080
those guys were always fighting. They were
like snowboarders and skiers, or like the

00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:14.970
Westboro Baptist Church and everyone else.

00:02:14.970 --> 00:02:19.630
At its core, Islam is what we call a radical
reforming religion—just like Jesus and Moses

00:02:19.630 --> 00:02:25.050
sought to restore Abrahamic monotheism after
what they perceived as straying, so too did Muhammad.

00:02:25.050 --> 00:02:29.200
Muslims believe that God sent Muhammad as
the final prophet to bring people back to

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:36.100
the one true religion, which involves the worship of,
and submission to, a single and all-powerful God.

00:02:36.100 --> 00:02:40.230
The Quran also acknowledges Abraham and Moses
and Jesus among others as prophets, but it’s

00:02:40.230 --> 00:02:42.360
very different from the Hebrew and Christian
bibles:

00:02:42.360 --> 00:02:44.300
For one thing it’s much less narrative,
but also its

00:02:44.300 --> 00:02:48.110
the written record of the revelations Muhammad
received—which means its not written from

00:02:48.110 --> 00:02:52.209
the point of view of people, it is seen as
the actual word of God.

00:02:52.209 --> 00:02:55.640
The Quran is a really broad-ranging text,
but it returns again and again to a couple

00:02:55.640 --> 00:03:01.030
themes. One is strict monotheism and the other
is the importance of taking care of those

00:03:01.030 --> 00:03:04.020
less fortunate than you. The Quran, says of
the good person

00:03:04.020 --> 00:03:08.610
spends his substance—however much he himself
may cherish it—upon his near of kin, and

00:03:08.610 --> 00:03:13.560
the orphans, and the needy, and the wayfarer,
and the beggars, and for the freeing of human

00:03:13.560 --> 00:03:14.990
beings from bondage.

00:03:14.990 --> 00:03:18.790
These revelations also radically increased
the rights of women and orphans, which was

00:03:18.790 --> 00:03:22.590
one of the reasons why Mohammad’s tribal
leaders weren’t that psyched about them.

00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:25.200
To talk more about Islamic faith and practice,
let’s go to the Thought Bubble.

00:03:25.200 --> 00:03:29.770
The five pillars of Islam are the basic acts
considered obligatory, at least by Sunni Muslims.

00:03:29.770 --> 00:03:32.440
First is the shahada or the profession of
the faith:

00:03:32.440 --> 00:03:37.300
There is no god but god and Muhammad is God’s
prophet, which is sometimes translated as

00:03:37.300 --> 00:03:40.790
“There is no god but Allah and Muhammad
is Allah’s prophet”, which tries to make

00:03:40.790 --> 00:03:44.770
Muslims sound other and ignores the fact that
the Arabic word for god—whether you are

00:03:44.770 --> 00:03:47.280
Christian or Jewish or Muslim—is Allah.

00:03:47.280 --> 00:03:53.670
Second, salat, or ritual prayer five times
a day—at dawn, noon, afternoon, sunset,

00:03:53.670 --> 00:03:58.310
and late evening—which are obligatory unless
you haven’t hit puberty, are too sick, or

00:03:58.310 --> 00:04:00.930
are menstruating. Keep it PG, Thought Bubble.

00:04:00.930 --> 00:04:04.989
Third, sawm, the month-long fast during the
month of Ramadan, in which Muslims do not

00:04:04.989 --> 00:04:08.239
eat or drink or smoke cigarettes during daylight
hours.

00:04:08.239 --> 00:04:12.760
Since Ramadan is a lunar-calendar month, it
moves around the seasons, and obviously it’s

00:04:12.760 --> 00:04:16.780
most fun during the winter, when days are
shorter, and least fun during the summer,

00:04:16.780 --> 00:04:19.100
when days are both long and hot.

00:04:19.100 --> 00:04:23.600
Fourth is zakat, or almsgiving, in which non-poor
Muslims are required to give a percentage

00:04:23.600 --> 00:04:25.470
of their income to the poor,

00:04:25.470 --> 00:04:30.680
and lastly hajj, the pilgrimage to Mecca that
Muslims must try to fulfill at least once

00:04:30.680 --> 00:04:33.660
in their lives, provided they are healthy
and have enough money.

00:04:33.660 --> 00:04:37.030
And there’s also more to understanding Islam
than just knowing the Quran. Like Judaism

00:04:37.030 --> 00:04:41.980
with its Talmud, and Christianity with its
lives of saints and writings of Church fathers,

00:04:41.980 --> 00:04:46.889
Islam has supplementary sacred texts, chief
among which is the hadith, a collection of

00:04:46.889 --> 00:04:49.230
sayings and stories about the Prophet.

00:04:49.230 --> 00:04:51.670
Thanks Thought Bubble. Oh, it’s time for
the open letter?

00:04:54.740 --> 00:04:55.560
